cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the design of distributed optimization algorithms for communication networks, which involves topics such as network information theory, network optimization, and control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of control theory could also place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with distributed algorithms, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
